<Paragraph>
This sample showcases how to insert and update the Table of Contents (TOC) in a Word document using Essential DocIO. TOC is a field which acts as an index to the Word document.
 </Paragraph>

<Paragraph TextAlignment ="Center">
<Image Source="Images\sample.png" Height="530" Stretch="None"/> 
</Paragraph>

<Paragraph Style="{DynamicResource HeaderParagraphStyle}">Features:</Paragraph> 
<List>
<ListItem><Paragraph> 	Supports inserting TOC into a Word document.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph> 	Supports inserting TOC based on default heading or custom styles.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph> 	Supports including page numbers and align-to-right options.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph>	Supports hyperlinks from TOC to navigate the document.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph> 	Supports setting of outline levels.</Paragraph></ListItem>
<ListItem><Paragraph> 	Supports updating Table of Contents.</Paragraph></ListItem></List>  

</FlowDocument>
